{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888463568,"sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","part":{"id":"prt_d7b337479001gqYUeoVc3tciv5","messageID":"msg_d7b3355dc001yeL7yTBIcdeZZ7","sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-2d74c316671240ccbca874321901a392","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n4: \n5: ## Dify plugin — file map\n6: \n7: | File | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n10: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n11: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n12: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n13: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n14: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n15: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n16: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n17: \n18: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n19: \n20: From source:\n21: \n22: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n23: - `type`: `plugin`\n24: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n25: - `name`: `agentcube`\n26: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n27: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n28: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n29: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n30: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n31: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n32: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n33: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n34: \n35: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n36: \n37: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n38: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n39: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n40: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n41: \n42: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n43: \n44: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n45: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n46: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n47: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n48: \n49: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n50: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n51: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n52: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n53: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n54: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n55: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n56: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n57: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n58: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n59: \n60: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n61: \n62: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n66: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n67: \n68: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n69:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n70:         try:\n71:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n72:         except Exception as e:\n73:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n74: ```\n75: \n76: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n77: \n78: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n79: \n80: ```python\n81: from collections.abc import Generator\n82: from typing import Any\n83: from dify_plugin import Tool\n84: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n85: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n86: \n87: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n88:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n89:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n90:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n91: \n92:     def execute(\n93:         self,\n94:         router_url=None,\n95:         workload_manager_url=None,\n96:         language=\"python\",\n97:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n98:         session_id=None,\n99:         code=None,\n100:         command=None,\n101:         session_reuse=False,\n102:         **kwargs\n103:     ): ...\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n107: \n108: ```\n109: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n110: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ## PCAP analyzer — application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n114: \n115: | File | Role |\n116: |------|------|\n117: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n118: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n119: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n120: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n121: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n122: \n123: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n124: \n125: ### Globals / config (selected)\n126: \n127: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n128: |------|--------|-----------------|\n129: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n130: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n131: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n132: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n133: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n134: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n135: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n136: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n137: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n138: \n139: ### Core classes / functions\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: class SandboxRunner:\n143:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n144:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n145:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n146:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n147:     def stop(self): ...\n148: \n149: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n150: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n151: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n152: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n153: \n154: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n155: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n156: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n157: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n158: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n159: \n160: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n161:     script: str\n162:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n163:     report: str\n164: \n165: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### FastAPI endpoints\n169: \n170: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n171: |--------|------|----------------------|\n172: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n173: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n174: \n175: ### Imports of note\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n179: from pydantic import BaseModel\n180: import uvicorn\n181: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n182: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n183: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n184: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n185: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n189: \n190: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n191: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n192: - Container port `8000` TCP\n193: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n194: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n195: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n196: \n197: ## Dockerfile highlights\n198: \n199: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n200: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n201: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n202: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n203: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n204: \n205: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n206: \n207: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n208: \n209: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Dify plugin — file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n| `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n\n## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n\nFrom source:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775888463549,"end":1775888463566}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888463572,"sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","part":{"id":"prt_d7b33769d001GSYsuXVOb30S74","messageID":"msg_d7b3355dc001yeL7yTBIcdeZZ7","sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cd9bae9a5c474db892c2436addf7aa0f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The SDK HTTP 底层客户端 provides the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling communication with the Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane) for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `sdk-python`  \n8: **Language:** Python  \n9: **Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`  \n10: **Size:** M\n11: \n12: ## Architecture\n13: \n14: ### Components\n15: \n16: | Component | Location | Responsibility |\n17: |-----------|----------|----------------|\n18: | `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Creates pooled requests.Session with HTTPAdapter |\n19: | `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Reads authentication token from file |\n20: | `get_logger` | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Provides configured logger instances |\n21: | `ControlPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | HTTP client for Workload Manager API |\n22: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Code Interpreter Router API |\n23: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Agent Runtime Router API |\n24: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | High-level Code Interpreter client |\n25: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | High-level Agent Runtime client |\n26: \n27: ### Data Flow\n28: \n29: ```\n30: Control Plane Flow:\n31: ControlPlaneClient → requests.Session → Workload Manager API\n32:                        ↓\n33:                   Connection Pooling\n34:                   HTTPAdapter (http/https)\n35: \n36: Data Plane Flow (Code Interpreter):\n37: CodeInterpreterClient → CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient → requests.Session → Router API\n38:                                                            ↓\n39:                                                       Connection Pooling\n40:                                                       HTTPAdapter (http/https)\n41: \n42: Data Plane Flow (Agent Runtime):\n43: AgentRuntimeClient → AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient → requests.Session → Router API\n44:                                                          ↓\n45:                                                     Connection Pooling\n46:                                                     HTTPAdapter (http/https)\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ## Package Structure\n50: \n51: ```\n52: agentcube-sdk/\n53: ├── pyproject.toml                    # Package metadata and dependencies\n54: ├── agentcube/\n55: │   ├── __init__.py                   # Public API exports\n56: │   ├── code_interpreter.py           # CodeInterpreterClient\n57: │   ├── agent_runtime.py              # AgentRuntimeClient\n58: │   ├── exceptions.py                 # Exception hierarchy\n59: │   ├── clients/\n60: │   │   ├── __init__.py              # Client re-exports\n61: │   │   ├── control_plane.py         # ControlPlaneClient\n62: │   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n63: │   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n64: │   └── utils/\n65: │       ├── __init__.py              # Module marker\n66: │       ├── http.py                  # create_session\n67: │       ├── utils.py                 # read_token_from_file\n68: │       └── log.py                   # get_logger\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Detailed Implementation\n72: \n73: ### 1. HTTP Session Management (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n74: \n75: ```python\n76: def create_session(\n77:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n78:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n79: ) -> requests.Session:\n80:     \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with connection pooling.\n81: \n82:     Args:\n83:         pool_connections: Number of connection pools to cache\n84:         pool_maxsize: Maximum number of connections in pool\n85: \n86:     Returns:\n87:         Configured requests.Session with HTTPAdapter mounted\n88:     \"\"\"\n89: ```\n90: \n91: **Implementation Details:**\n92: - Creates `requests.Session` instance\n93: - Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n94: - Configures connection pooling with specified parameters\n95: - Returns session ready for use\n96: \n97: **Connection Pooling Benefits:**\n98: - Reuses TCP connections for multiple requests to same host\n99: - Reduces latency from TCP handshake and TLS negotiation\n100: - Limits resource usage with pool size constraints\n101: \n102: ### 2. Token Management (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n103: \n104: ```python\n105: def read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n106:     \"\"\"Read authentication token from file.\n107: \n108:     Args:\n109:         file_path: Path to token file (e.g., K8s service account token)\n110: \n111:     Returns:\n112:         Token string stripped of whitespace\n113: \n114:     Note:\n115:         Returns empty string on FileNotFoundError to support\n116:         optional authentication scenarios\n117:     \"\"\"\n118: ```\n119: \n120: **Implementation Details:**\n121: - Opens and reads file contents\n122: - Strips whitespace from token\n123: - Returns empty string if file not found (graceful degradation)\n124: - Used for Kubernetes service account token: `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n125: \n126: ### 3. Logger Configuration (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n127: \n128: ```python\n129: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n130:     \"\"\"Get configured logger instance.\n131: \n132:     Args:\n133:         name: Logger name (typically __name__)\n134:         level: Logging level (default: logging.INFO)\n135: \n136:     Returns:\n137:         Configured logger instance\n138:     \"\"\"\n139: ```\n140: \n141: **Implementation Details:**\n142: - Creates or retrieves logger by name\n143: - Sets specified logging level\n144: - Returns logger ready for use\n145: - Supports both integer and string level specifications\n146: \n147: ### 4. ControlPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n148: \n149: #### Class Structure\n150: \n151: ```python\n152: class ControlPlaneClient:\n153:     def __init__(\n154:         self,\n155:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n156:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n157:         timeout: int = 120,\n158:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n159:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n160:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n161:     ):\n162:         \"\"\"Initialize control plane client.\n163: \n164:         Args:\n165:             workload_manager_url: Base URL for Workload Manager API\n166:                                   (defaults to WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var)\n167:             auth_token: Authentication token (defaults to SA token file)\n168:             timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n169:             connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n170:             pool_connections: Connection pool size (default: 10)\n171:             pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool (default: 10)\n172:         \"\"\"\n173: ```\n174: \n175: **Initialization Logic:**\n176: 1. Resolve `workload_manager_url` from parameter or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n177: 2. Resolve `auth_token` from parameter or service account token file\n178: 3. Store timeout configuration\n179: 4. Create session with connection pooling\n180: 5. Configure default headers: `Content-Type: application/json`\n181: 6. If token present, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header\n182: \n183: #### Session Creation\n184: \n185: ```python\n186: def create_session(\n187:     name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n188:     namespace: str = \"default\",\n189:     metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n190:     ttl: int = 3600,\n191: ) -> str:\n192:     \"\"\"Create a new Code Interpreter session.\n193: \n194:     Args:\n195:         name: Session name\n196:         namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n197:         metadata: Optional metadata dictionary\n198:         ttl: Time-to-live in seconds (default: 3600)\n199: \n200:     Returns:\n201:         Session ID string\n202: \n203:     Raises:\n204:         ValueError: If sessionId not in response\n205:         requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n206:     \"\"\"\n207: ```\n208: \n209: **HTTP Details:**\n210: - **Method:** `POST`\n211: - **Path:** `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n212: - **Headers:** `Content-Type: application/json`, `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token)\n213: - **Body:** JSON `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}`\n214: - **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n215: - **Response:** JSON with `sessionId` field\n216: \n217: #### Session Deletion\n218: \n219: ```python\n220: def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n221:     \"\"\"Delete a Code Interpreter session.\n222: \n223:     Args:\n224:         session_id: Session ID to delete\n225: \n226:     Returns:\n227:         True if deletion succeeded (including 404), False otherwise\n228: \n229:     Note:\n230:         404 responses are treated as success (idempotent delete)\n231:     \"\"\"\n232: ```\n233: \n234: **HTTP Details:**\n235: - **Method:** `DELETE`\n236: - **Path:** `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n237: - **Headers:** Same as session creation\n238: - **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n239: - **Response Handling:**\n240:   - Returns `True` on 200, 404 (not found considered success)\n241:   - Returns `False` on other errors\n242:   - Logs errors before returning\n243: \n244: #### Cleanup\n245: \n246: ```python\n247: def close(self) -> None:\n248:     \"\"\"Close the HTTP session and release resources.\"\"\"\n249:     self.session.close()\n250: ```\n251: \n252: ### 5. CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n253: \n254: #### Class Structure\n255: \n256: ```python\n257: class CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n258:     def __init__(\n259:         self,\n260:         session_id: str,\n261:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n262:         namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n263:         cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n264:         base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n265:         timeout: int = 120,\n266:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n267:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n268:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n269:     ):\n270:         \"\"\"Initialize Code Interpreter data plane client.\n271: \n272:         Args:\n273:             session_id: Session ID for header\n274:             router_url: Router base URL (used if base_url not provided)\n275:             namespace: Namespace for URL construction\n276:             cr_name: Custom resource name for URL construction\n277:             base_url: Full base URL (overrides URL construction)\n278:             timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n279:             connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n280:             pool_connections: Connection pool size (default: 10)\n281:             pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool (default: 10)\n282:         \"\"\"\n283: ```\n284: \n285: **Base URL Resolution:**\n286: ```python\n287: if base_url is None:\n288:     base_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n289:     self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n290: else:\n291:     self.base_url = base_url\n292: ```\n293: \n294: **Session Configuration:**\n295: - Creates session with connection pooling\n296: - Sets default header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n297: \n298: #### Request Helper\n299: \n300: ```python\n301: def _request(\n302:     self,\n303:     method: str,\n304:     endpoint: str,\n305:     body: Optional[bytes] = None,\n306:     **kwargs\n307: ) -> requests.Response:\n308:     \"\"\"Execute HTTP request with session header.\n309: \n310:     Args:\n311:         method: HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.)\n312:         endpoint: Relative path to base_url\n313:         body: Optional request body as bytes\n314:         **kwargs: Additional arguments for requests.request\n315: \n316:     Returns:\n317:         requests.Response object\n318:     \"\"\"\n319: ```\n320: \n321: **Implementation:**\n322: - Constructs full URL: `urljoin(self.base_url, endpoint)`\n323: - Includes session header automatically\n324: - Sets `Content-Type: application/json` if body provided\n325: - Uses timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n326: - Passes through additional kwargs to requests\n327: \n328: #### Command Execution\n329: \n330: ```python\n331: def execute_command(\n332:     self,\n333:     command: Union[str, List[str]],\n334:     timeout: Optional[float] = None\n335: ) -> str:\n336:     \"\"\"Execute command in Code Interpreter session.\n337: \n338:     Args:\n339:         command: Command string or list of arguments\n340:         timeout: Command timeout in seconds (None for default)\n341: \n342:     Returns:\n343:         Command stdout output\n344: \n345:     Raises:\n346:         CommandExecutionError: If command exits with non-zero code\n347:         requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n348:     \"\"\"\n349: ```\n350: \n351: **HTTP Details:**\n352: - **Method:** `POST`\n353: - **Path:** `api/execute`\n354: - **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n355: - **Body:** JSON `{\"command\": [arg1, arg2, ...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}`\n356: - **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout_value + 2.0)` (buffer for PicoD exit 124)\n357: - **Response Processing:**\n358:   - Parse JSON response\n359:   - Check `exit_code` field\n360:   - Raise `CommandExecutionError` if non-zero\n361:   - Return `stdout` on success\n362: \n363: #### File Operations\n364: \n365: **Write File:**\n366: ```python\n367: def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n368:     \"\"\"Write content to remote file.\n369: \n370:     Args:\n371:         content: File content as string\n372:         remote_path: Remote file path\n373: \n374:     Raises:\n375:         DataPlaneError: On write failure\n376:     \"\"\"\n377: ```\n378: - **Method:** `POST`\n379: - **Path:** `api/files`\n380: - **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n381: - **Body:** JSON `{\"path\": remote_path, \"content\": base64(content), \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n382: \n383: **Upload File:**\n384: ```python\n385: def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n386:     \"\"\"Upload local file to remote path.\n387: \n388:     Args:\n389:         local_path: Local file path\n390:         remote_path: Remote file path\n391: \n392:     Raises:\n393:         FileNotFoundError: If local file doesn't exist\n394:         DataPlaneError: On upload failure\n395:     \"\"\"\n396: ```\n397: - **Method:** `POST`\n398: - **Path:** `api/files`\n399: - **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id` (explicitly set, no JSON Content-Type)\n400: - **Body:** Multipart form data\n401:   - `files`: `{'file': (filename, file_handle)}`\n402:   - `data`: `{'path': remote_path, 'mode': '0644'}`\n403: \n404: **Download File:**\n405: ```python\n406: def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n407:     \"\"\"Download remote file to local path.\n408: \n409:     Args:\n410:         remote_path: Remote file path\n411:         local_path: Local file path\n412: \n413:     Raises:\n414:         DataPlaneError: On download failure\n415:     \"\"\"\n416: ```\n417: - **Method:** `GET`\n418: - **Path:** `api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n419: - **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`\n420: - **Stream:** `True` (for efficient large file download)\n421: - **Body:** Writes response content to local file\n422: \n423: **List Files:**\n424: ```python\n425: def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n426:     \"\"\"List files in remote path.\n427: \n428:     Args:\n429:         path: Remote path (default: \".\")\n430: \n431:     Returns:\n432:         Directory listing structure\n433: \n434:     Raises:\n435:         DataPlaneError: On list failure\n436:     \"\"\"\n437: ```\n438: - **Method:** `GET`\n439: - **Path:** `api/files?path={path}`\n440: - **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id`\n441: - **Response:** JSON with directory contents\n442: \n443: #### Code Execution\n444: \n445: ```python\n446: def run_code(\n447:     self,\n448:     language: str,\n449:     code: str,\n450:     timeout: Optional[float] = None\n451: ) -> str:\n452:     \"\"\"Execute code in specified language.\n453: \n454:     Args:\n455:         language: Programming language (python, python3, py)\n456:         code: Code to execute\n457:         timeout: Execution timeout in seconds\n458: \n459:     Returns:\n460:         Code execution output\n461: \n462:     Note:\n463:         For Python, writes timestamped .py file and executes via execute_command\n464:     \"\"\"\n465: ```\n466: \n467: **Python Code Path:**\n468: 1. Check if language is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n469: 2. Generate timestamped filename: `code_{timestamp}.py`\n470: 3. Call `write_file(code, filename)`\n471: 4. Call `execute_command([\"python3\", filename], timeout)`\n472: 5. Return output\n473: \n474: ### 6. AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n475: \n476: #### Class Structure\n477: \n478: ```python\n479: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n480:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n481: \n482:     def __init__(\n483:         self,\n484:         router_url: str,\n485:         namespace: str,\n486:         agent_name: str,\n487:         timeout: int = 120,\n488:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n489:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n490:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n491:     ):\n492:         \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime data plane client.\n493: \n494:         Args:\n495:             router_url: Router base URL\n496:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n497:             agent_name: Agent name\n498:             timeout: Read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n499:             connect_timeout: Connect timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n500:             pool_connections: Connection pool size (default: 10)\n501:             pool_maxsize: Max connections per pool (default: 10)\n502:         \"\"\"\n503: ```\n504: \n505: **Base URL Construction:**\n506: ```python\n507: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n508: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n509: ```\n510: \n511: **Session Configuration:**\n512: - Creates session with connection pooling\n513: - Sets default header: `{SESSION_HEADER}: {session_id}`\n514: \n515: #### Session Bootstrap\n516: \n517: ```python\n518: def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n519:     \"\"\"Bootstrap session ID from Agent Runtime endpoint.\n520: \n521:     Returns:\n522:         Session ID from response header\n523: \n524:     Raises:\n525:         ValueError: If session_id header not present\n526:         requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n527:     \"\"\"\n528: ```\n529: \n530: **HTTP Details:**\n531: - **Method:** `GET`\n532: - **Path:** `self.base_url` (full invocation URL)\n533: - **Headers:** None (session not yet known)\n534: - **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n535: - **Response Processing:**\n536:   - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n537:   - Raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` if missing\n538:   - Return session ID\n539: \n540: #### Agent Invocation\n541: \n542: ```python\n543: def invoke(\n544:     self,\n545:     session_id: str,\n546:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n547:     timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n548: ) -> requests.Response:\n549:     \"\"\"Invoke agent with payload.\n550: \n551:     Args:\n552:         session_id: Session ID for header\n553:         payload: Agent invocation payload (JSON-serializable)\n554:         timeout: Request timeout in seconds (None for default)\n555: \n556:     Returns:\n557:         requests.Response object\n558: \n559:     Raises:\n560:         ValueError: If session_id is falsy\n561:         requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n562:     \"\"\"\n563: ```\n564: \n565: **HTTP Details:**\n566: - **Method:** `POST`\n567: - **Path:** `self.base_url`\n568: - **Headers:** `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n569: - **Body:** JSON payload\n570: - **Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout_value or self.timeout)`\n571: - **Validation:** Raises `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` if session_id falsy\n572: \n573: ### 7. High-Level Clients\n574: \n575: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n576: \n577: ```python\n578: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n579:     def __init__(\n580:         self,\n581:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n582:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n583:         ttl: int = 3600,\n584:         workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n585:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n586:         auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n587:         verbose: bool = False,\n588:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n589:     ):\n590:         \"\"\"Initialize Code Interpreter client.\n591: \n592:         Args:\n593:             name: Session name\n594:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n595:             ttl: Session time-to-live in seconds\n596:             workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL\n597:             router_url: Router URL (required, or ROUTER_URL env var)\n598:             auth_token: Authentication token\n599:             verbose: Enable verbose logging\n600:             session_id: Existing session ID (skip creation if provided)\n601:         \"\"\"\n602: ```\n603: \n604: **Initialization Flow:**\n605: 1. Validate `router_url` (raise ValueError if missing)\n606: 2. Store configuration\n607: 3. Create logger\n608: 4. Initialize `ControlPlaneClient`\n609: 5. If `session_id` not provided:\n610:    - Call `create_session()` via control plane\n611:    - Store new session ID\n612: 6. Call `_init_data_plane()` to create data plane client\n613: \n614: **Context Manager:**\n615: ```python\n616: def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\":\n617:     return self\n618: \n619: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n620:     self.stop()\n621: ```\n622: \n623: **Stop/Cleanup:**\n624: ```python\n625: def stop(self) -> None:\n626:     \"\"\"Stop Code Interpreter session.\n627: \n628:     Closes data plane, deletes control plane session (if created),\n629:     and closes control plane HTTP session.\n630:     \"\"\"\n631: ```\n632: \n633: **Delegate Methods:**\n634: - `execute_command(command, timeout)` → data plane\n635: - `run_code(language, code, timeout)` → data plane\n636: - `write_file(content, remote_path)` → data plane\n637: - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` → data plane\n638: - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` → data plane\n639: - `list_files(path)` → data plane\n640: \n641: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n642: \n643: ```python\n644: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n645:     def __init__(\n646:         self,\n647:         agent_name: str,\n648:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n649:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n650:         verbose: bool = False,\n651:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n652:         timeout: int = 120,\n653:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n654:     ):\n655:         \"\"\"Initialize Agent Runtime client.\n656: \n657:         Args:\n658:             agent_name: Agent name\n659:             namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n660:             router_url: Router URL (or ROUTER_URL env var)\n661:             verbose: Enable verbose logging\n662:             session_id: Existing session ID\n663:             timeout: Default request timeout\n664:             connect_timeout: Connect timeout\n665:         \"\"\"\n666: ```\n667: \n668: **Initialization Flow:**\n669: 1. Store configuration\n670: 2. Create logger\n671: 3. Initialize `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n672: 4. If `session_id` not provided:\n673:    - Call `bootstrap_session_id()` to get session from endpoint\n674:    - Store new session ID\n675: \n676: **Context Manager:**\n677: ```python\n678: def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n679:     return self\n680: \n681: def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n682:     self.close()\n683: ```\n684: \n685: **Invoke:**\n686: ```python\n687: def invoke(\n688:     self,\n689:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n690:     timeout: Optional[float] = None\n691: ) -> Any:\n692:     \"\"\"Invoke agent with payload.\n693: \n694:     Args:\n695:         payload: Agent invocation payload\n696:         timeout: Request timeout (None for default)\n697: \n698:     Returns:\n699:         Agent response\n700: \n701:     Raises:\n702:         ValueError: If session_id not initialized\n703:         requests.exceptions.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n704:     \"\"\"\n705: ```\n706: \n707: **Close:**\n708: ```python\n709: def close(self) -> None:\n710:     \"\"\"Close HTTP session and release resources.\"\"\"\n711:     self.dp_client.close()\n712: ```\n713: \n714: ### 8. Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n715: \n716: ```python\n717: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n718:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n719:     pass\n720: \n721: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n722:     \"\"\"Raised when command execution fails with non-zero exit code.\"\"\"\n723:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n724:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n725:         self.stderr = stderr\n726:         self.command = command\n727:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n728: \n729: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n730:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\"\"\"\n731:     pass\n732: \n733: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n734:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\"\"\"\n735:     pass\n736: ```\n737: \n738: **Exception Usage:**\n739: - `CommandExecutionError`: Raised by `execute_command()` on non-zero exit\n740: - `SessionError`: Defined for extension (not currently raised by core)\n741: - `DataPlaneError`: Defined for extension (not currently raised by core)\n742: - `ValueError`: Used for invalid configuration (e.g., missing URLs)\n743: - `requests.exceptions`: Used for HTTP errors\n744: \n745: ### 9. Configuration Resolution\n746: \n747: #### ControlPlaneClient Configuration\n748: \n749: | Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n750: |---------|-----------------|---------|\n751: | `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Required |\n752: | `Authorization` | `auth_token` → `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` | Optional |\n753: | `timeout` | Constructor parameter | 120 |\n754: | `connect_timeout` | Constructor parameter | 5.0 |\n755: | `pool_connections` | Constructor parameter | 10 |\n756: | `pool_maxsize` | Constructor parameter | 10 |\n757: \n758: #### CodeInterpreterClient Configuration\n759: \n760: | Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n761: |---------|-----------------|---------|\n762: | `router_url` | Constructor → `ROUTER_URL` | Required |\n763: | `workload_manager_url` | Constructor → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Optional |\n764: | `auth_token` | Constructor → SA token file | Optional |\n765: | `name` | Constructor | \"my-interpreter\" |\n766: | `namespace` | Constructor | \"default\" |\n767: | `ttl` | Constructor | 3600 |\n768: | `verbose` | Constructor | False |\n769: | `session_id` | Constructor (skip creation) | Auto-created |\n770: | `timeout` | Constructor | 120 |\n771: | `connect_timeout` | Constructor | 5.0 |\n772: \n773: #### AgentRuntimeClient Configuration\n774: \n775: | Setting | Resolution Order | Default |\n776: |---------|-----------------|---------|\n777: | `router_url` | Constructor → `ROUTER_URL` | Required |\n778: | `agent_name` | Constructor | Required |\n779: | `namespace` | Constructor | \"default\" |\n780: | `verbose` | Constructor | False |\n781: | `session_id` | Constructor (skip bootstrap) | Auto-bootstrapped |\n782: | `timeout` | Constructor | 120 |\n783: | `connect_timeout` | Constructor | 5.0 |\n784: \n785: ## HTTP API Contracts\n786: \n787: ### Control Plane API\n788: \n789: #### Create Session\n790: \n791: ```http\n792: POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter\n793: Content-Type: application/json\n794: Authorization: Bearer {token}\n795: \n796: {\n797:   \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n798:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n799:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n800:   \"metadata\": {\n801:     \"key\": \"value\"\n802:   }\n803: }\n804: ```\n805: \n806: **Response:**\n807: ```json\n808: {\n809:   \"sessionId\": \"abc123def456\"\n810: }\n811: ```\n812: \n813: #### Delete Session\n814: \n815: ```http\n816: DELETE {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}\n817: Content-Type: application/json\n818: Authorization: Bearer {token}\n819: ```\n820: \n821: **Response:** 200 OK or 404 Not Found\n822: \n823: ### Code Interpreter Data Plane API\n824: \n825: #### Execute Command\n826: \n827: ```http\n828: POST {base_url}/api/execute\n829: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n830: Content-Type: application/json\n831: \n832: {\n833:   \"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"],\n834:   \"timeout\": \"60s\"\n835: }\n836: ```\n837: \n838: **Response:**\n839: ```json\n840: {\n841:   \"exit_code\": 0,\n842:   \"stdout\": \"output\",\n843:   \"stderr\": \"error output\"\n844: }\n845: ```\n846: \n847: #### Write File\n848: \n849: ```http\n850: POST {base_url}/api/files\n851: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n852: Content-Type: application/json\n853: \n854: {\n855:   \"path\": \"/path/to/file.txt\",\n856:   \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\",  // base64 encoded\n857:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n858: }\n859: ```\n860: \n861: **Response:** 200 OK\n862: \n863: #### Upload File\n864: \n865: ```http\n866: POST {base_url}/api/files\n867: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n868: \n869: Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary\n870: \n871: ------WebKitFormBoundary\n872: Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"file\"; filename=\"local.txt\"\n873: Content-Type: application/octet-stream\n874: \n875: [file contents]\n876: ------WebKitFormBoundary\n877: Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"path\"\n878: \n879: /path/to/remote.txt\n880: ------WebKitFormBoundary\n881: Content-Disposition: form-data; name=\"mode\"\n882: \n883: 0644\n884: ------WebKitFormBoundary--\n885: ```\n886: \n887: **Response:** 200 OK\n888: \n889: #### Download File\n890: \n891: ```http\n892: GET {base_url}/api/files/path/to/file.txt\n893: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n894: ```\n895: \n896: **Response:** File content streamed\n897: \n898: #### List Files\n899: \n900: ```http\n901: GET {base_url}/api/files?path=/path\n902: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n903: ```\n904: \n905: **Response:**\n906: ```json\n907: {\n908:   \"files\": [\n909:     {\"name\": \"file1.txt\", \"size\": 1024, \"mode\": \"0644\"},\n910:     {\"name\": \"file2.py\", \"size\": 2048, \"mode\": \"0755\"}\n911:   ]\n912: }\n913: ```\n914: \n915: ### Agent Runtime Data Plane API\n916: \n917: #### Bootstrap Session\n918: \n919: ```http\n920: GET {base_url}\n921: ```\n922: \n923: **Response Headers:**\n924: ```\n925: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n926: ```\n927: \n928: #### Invoke Agent\n929: \n930: ```http\n931: POST {base_url}\n932: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n933: Content-Type: application/json\n934: \n935: {\n936:   \"input\": \"user input\",\n937:   \"context\": {}\n938: }\n939: ```\n940: \n941: **Response:** Agent-specific JSON response\n942: \n943: ## Dependencies\n944: \n945: ### Runtime Dependencies (`pyproject.toml`)\n946: \n947: ```toml\n948: dependencies = [\n949:     \"requests\",\n950:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n951:     \"cryptography\",\n952: ]\n953: ```\n954: \n955: **Dependency Details:**\n956: - `requests`: HTTP client library for API communication\n957: - `PyJWT>=2.0.0`: JWT token handling (for future JWT-based auth)\n958: - `cryptography`: Cryptographic utilities (for JWT operations)\n959: \n960: ### Build Configuration\n961: \n962: ```toml\n963: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n964: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n965: \n966: [build-system]\n967: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n968: \n969: [tool.setuptools]\n970: packages = [\"agentcube\"]\n971: \n972: [tool.setuptools.package-data]\n973: agentcube = [\"py.typed\"]\n974: ```\n975: \n976: **Package Configuration:**\n977: - Minimum Python: 3.10\n978: - Build system: setuptools\n979: - Package inclusion: All `agentcube*` files\n980: - Type hints included for better IDE support\n981: \n982: ## Testing Strategy\n983: \n984: ### Unit Tests Required\n985: \n986: | Component | Test Cases |\n987: |-----------|------------|\n988: | `create_session()` | - Session creation with default pooling<br>- Custom pool sizes<br>- HTTPAdapter mounted for both http/https |\n989: | `read_token_from_file()` | - Read existing token file<br>- FileNotFoundError returns empty string<br>- Whitespace stripping |\n990: | `get_logger()` | - Logger creation with default level<br>- Custom level (int and string)<br>- Logger name propagation |\n991: | `ControlPlaneClient.__init__()` | - URL resolution from parameter and env<br>- Token resolution from parameter and file<br>- Session header configuration<br>- Missing required URL |\n992: | `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` | - Successful session creation<br>- Extract sessionId from response<br>- Missing sessionId raises ValueError<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n993: | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` | - Successful deletion (200)<br>- 404 treated as success<br>- Other errors logged and return False |\n994: | `ControlPlaneClient.close()` | - Session cleanup |\n995: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__()` | - Base URL construction from components<br>- Base URL override<br>- Session header configuration |\n996: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()` | - Successful command execution<br>- Non-zero exit raises CommandExecutionError<br>- Timeout buffer calculation<br>- Command string and list handling |\n997: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()` | - Base64 encoding<br>- Successful write<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n998: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()` | - Multipart form construction<br>- Session header on upload<br>- File not found raises FileNotFoundError |\n999: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()` | - Streaming download<br>- Path cleaning (lstrip)<br>- File writing |\n1000: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()` | - Query parameter construction<br>- Successful list<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n1001: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()` | - Base URL construction<br>- Session header constant |\n1002: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` | - Successful bootstrap<br>- Missing header raises ValueError<br>- HTTP errors propagate |\n1003: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()` | - Successful invocation<br>- Missing session_id raises ValueError<br>- Timeout handling<br>- JSON serialization |\n1004: | `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__()` | - Missing router_url raises ValueError<br>- Session creation via control plane<br>- Existing session_id reuse<br>- Data plane init failure cleanup |\n1005: | `CodeInterpreterClient.__enter__/__exit__()` | - Context manager protocol<br>- stop() called on exit |\n1006: | `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` | - Data plane closure<br>- Session deletion (if created)<br>- Control plane closure |\n1007: | `CodeInterpreterClient.execute_command()` | - Delegation to data plane<br>- CommandExecutionError propagation |\n1008: | `CodeInterpreterClient.run_code()` | - Python code path (write + execute)<br>- Other languages via data plane |\n1009: | `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()` | - Session bootstrap when not provided<br>- Existing session_id reuse |\n1010: | `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` | - Delegation to data plane<br>- Timeout handling |\n1011: | `AgentRuntimeClient.__enter__/__exit__()` | - Context manager protocol<br>- close() called on exit |\n1012: \n1013: ### Integration Tests\n1014: \n1015: | Scenario | Test Cases |\n1016: |----------|------------|\n1017: | End-to-end Code Interpreter | - Full session lifecycle<br>- Multiple operations<br>- Error recovery |\n1018: | End-to-end Agent Runtime | - Session bootstrap<br>- Multiple invocations<br>- Timeout handling |\n1019: | Concurrent clients | - Multiple clients sharing connection pool<br>- Pool exhaustion handling |\n1020: | Network resilience | - Retry on transient failures<br>- Timeout behavior<br)- Connection pool reuse |\n1021: \n1022: ### Mock Tests\n1023: \n1024: - Mock `requests.Session` for HTTP calls\n1025: - Mock `ControlPlaneClient` in high-level clients\n1026: - Mock file I/O for token reading\n1027: - Mock logger for testing without side effects\n1028: \n1029: ## Security Considerations\n1030: \n1031: 1. **Token Handling:**\n1032:    - Tokens are read from K8s service account files in production\n1033:    - Tokens are never logged or exposed in error messages\n1034:    - Token file permissions should be 0600\n1035: \n1036: 2. **URL Validation:**\n1037:    - Validate URL format before use\n1038:    - Prevent URL injection attacks\n1039:    - Use HTTPS in production\n1040: \n1041: 3. **Header Management:**\n1042:    - Session headers are case-sensitive: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n1043:    - Headers are properly sanitized before use\n1044: \n1045: 4. **Path Security:**\n1046:    - File paths are sanitized before API calls\n1047:    - Path traversal prevented with `lstrip(\"/\")` for downloads\n1048: \n1049: 5. **Connection Pooling:**\n1050:    - Pool size limits prevent resource exhaustion\n1051:    - Connections are properly closed on cleanup\n1052: \n1053: 6. **Timeout Configuration:**\n1054:    - Timeouts prevent hanging requests\n1055:    - Connect and read timeouts are separate\n1056: \n1057: 7. **Error Messages:**\n1058:    - Sensitive data not included in error messages\n1059:    - Stack traces only in verbose mode\n1060: \n1061: ## Performance Considerations\n1062: \n1063: 1. **Connection Pooling:**\n1064:    - Reuses connections for multiple requests\n1065:    - Reduces TCP/TLS handshake overhead\n1066:    - Configurable pool sizes\n1067: \n1068: 2. **Timeout Management:**\n1069:    - Separate connect and read timeouts\n1070:    - Per-call timeout overrides\n1071:    - Timeout buffer for long-running commands\n1072: \n1073: 3. **Streaming Downloads:**\n1074:    - Large files streamed to memory\n1075:    - Prevents memory exhaustion\n1076:    - Efficient for big file downloads\n1077: \n1078: 4. **Session Reuse:**\n1079:    - HTTP session created once per client\n1080:    - Headers configured once\n1081:    - Reduced overhead for repeated calls\n1082: \n1083: 5. **Multipart Uploads:**\n1084:    - Efficient file upload mechanism\n1085:    - Minimal memory overhead\n1086: \n1087: ## Future Enhancements\n1088: \n1089: 1. **Retry Logic:**\n1090:    - Configurable retry on transient failures\n1091:    - Exponential backoff\n1092:    - Retry-specific exceptions\n1093: \n1094: 2. **Request Signing:**\n1095:    - JWT-based authentication\n1096:    - Request signature verification\n1097:    - Token refresh mechanism\n1098: \n1099: 3. **Metrics Collection:**\n1100:    - Request latency tracking\n1101:    - Error rate monitoring\n1102:    - Connection pool metrics\n1103: \n1104: 4. **Circuit Breaker:**\n1105:    - Prevent cascading failures\n1106:    - Automatic recovery\n1107:    - Configurable thresholds\n1108: \n1109: 5. **Async Support:**\n1110:    - `aiohttp` integration\n1111:    - Async context managers\n1112:    - Non-blocking I/O\n1113: \n1114: 6. **Advanced Logging:**\n1115:    - Request/response logging\n1116:    - Structured logging (JSON)\n1117:    - Log correlation IDs\n1118: \n1119: 7. **WebSocket Support:**\n1120:    - Real-time communication\n1121:    - Streaming responses\n1122:    - Keepalive handling\n1123: \n1124: 8. **Custom Adapters:**\n1125:    - Pluggable HTTP adapters\n1126:    - Custom retry strategies\n1127:    - Advanced connection management\n\n(End of file - total 1127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe SDK HTTP 底层客户端 provides the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling communication with the Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane) for Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services.\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Source Root:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Creates pooled requests.Session with HTTPAdapter |\n| `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Reads authentication token from file |\n| `get_logger` | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Provides configured logger instances |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775888463552,"end":1775888463569}}}}
