{"type":"text","timestamp":1775888783850,"sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","part":{"id":"prt_d7b34251e0012hiV1Mhd9RBHqh","messageID":"msg_d7b33e4190013AgY6LgIabSrtF","sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create the design.md file for AR-036 with comprehensive technical implementation details.","time":{"start":1775888783848,"end":1775888783848}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888783978,"sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3859eb00170ynQNQRQ4FW9D","messageID":"msg_d7b33e4190013AgY6LgIabSrtF","sessionID":"ses_284ccd635ffe4GuQ4tAfB2c7Yy","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-3b47e0ffc19e4524afd02b1a6037aa02","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Dify plugin integration enables AgentCube to be used as a tool within the Dify platform, providing secure code execution and file operations through AgentCube's code interpreter sandboxes. The plugin exposes a Dify-compatible Python plugin that integrates with the Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane) for creating and managing Code Interpreter sessions.\n\n**Module:** `integrations`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Source Reference:** `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| `main.py` | Plugin root | Plugin entrypoint and framework runner |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Plugin root | Root plugin metadata for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | `provider/` | Tool provider descriptor and tool list |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `provider/` | Tool provider implementation with credential validation |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | `tools/` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `tools/` | Tool implementation delegating to agentcube-sdk |\n| `requirements.txt` | Plugin root | Dependency pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md` | Plugin root | Documentation |\n| `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Plugin root | Privacy policy and packaging exclusions |\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nDify Platform Request\n        ↓\nDify Plugin Framework (dify-plugin)\n        ↓\nAgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider\n        ↓\nAgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke()\n        ↓\nTool.execute() → CodeInterpreterClient\n        ↓\nControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager)\n        ↓\nCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (Router)\n        ↓\nPicoD Sandbox (Kubernetes Pod)\n```\n\n### Plugin Lifecycle\n\n```\n1. Plugin Start\n   ↓\n2. Load manifest.yaml\n   ↓\n3. Register provider/agentcube.yaml\n   ↓\n4. Load provider/agentcube.py\n   ↓\n5. Register tools from provider\n   ↓\n6. Load tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml\n   ↓\n7. Load tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\n   ↓\n8. Plugin ready for tool invocations\n   ↓\n9. Handle tool requests\n   ↓\n10. Stop on platform signal\n```\n\n## Package Structure\n\n```\nintegrations/dify-plugin/\n├── main.py                          # Plugin entrypoint\n├── manifest.yaml                    # Root plugin manifest\n├── requirements.txt                 # Python dependencies\n├── GUIDE.md                         # User guide\n├── README.md                        # Plugin documentation\n├── PRIVACY.md                       # Privacy policy\n├── .difyignore                      # Packaging exclusions\n├── icon.png                         # Plugin icon (light)\n├── icon-dark.png                    # Plugin icon (dark)\n├── provider/\n│   └── agentcube.yaml               # Provider descriptor\n│   └── agentcube.py                 # Provider implementation\n└── tools/\n    └── agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml   # Tool schema\n    └── agentcube-code-interpreter.py     # Tool implementation\n\nexample/pcap-analyzer/\n├── pcap_analyzer.py                 # FastAPI application\n├── requirements.txt                 # Application dependencies\n├── Dockerfile                       # Container image definition\n├── deployment.yaml                  # Kubernetes deployment\n└── README.md                        # Example documentation\n```\n\n## Detailed Implementation\n\n### 1. Plugin Entrypoint (`main.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom dify_plugin import Plugin, DifyPluginEnv\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Main entrypoint for the Dify plugin.\n\n    Initializes the plugin framework with a maximum request timeout\n    of 120 seconds to allow for long-running code execution tasks.\n    \"\"\"\n    Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Uses `dify-plugin` framework's `Plugin` class\n- Configures `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120` seconds for code execution\n- Blocks until platform signals shutdown\n- Handles plugin lifecycle automatically\n\n### 2. Root Plugin Manifest (`manifest.yaml`)\n\n#### Required Top-Level Keys\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `version` | string | Plugin version (e.g., `0.0.2`) |\n| `type` | string | Must be `plugin` |\n| `author` | string | Author identifier (e.g., `volcano-sh`) |\n| `name` | string | Plugin internal name (e.g., `agentcube`) |\n| `label` | object | Multilingual label map |\n| `description` | object | Multilingual description map |\n| `icon` | string | Icon filename for light theme |\n| `icon_dark` | string | Icon filename for dark theme |\n| `resource` | object | Resource limits and permissions |\n| `plugins.tools` | list | List of provider descriptor paths |\n| `meta` | object | Version, arch, runner metadata |\n| `created_at` | string | Creation timestamp |\n| `privacy` | string | Privacy policy URL or text |\n| `repo` | string | Repository URL |\n| `verified` | boolean | Verification status |\n\n#### Example Structure\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"0.0.2\"\ntype: plugin\nauthor: volcano-sh\nname: agentcube\nlabel:\n  en_US: Agentcube\n  ja_JP: Agentcube\n  zh_Hans: Agentcube\n  pt_BR: Agentcube\ndescription:\n  en_US: AgentCube code interpreter integration for Dify\n  ja_JP: Dify用AgentCubeコードインタープリター統合\n  zh_Hans: AgentCube代码解释器Dify集成\n  pt_BR: Integração do interpretador de código AgentCube para Dify\nicon: icon.png\nicon_dark: icon-dark.png\nresource:\n  memory: 512Mi\n  permission:\n    tool:\n      enabled: true\n    model:\n      enabled: false\n    endpoint:\n      enabled: false\n    app:\n      enabled: false\n    storage:\n      enabled: false\nplugins:\n  tools:\n    - provider/agentcube.yaml\nmeta:\n  version: \"0.0.2\"\n  arch:\n    - amd64\n    - arm64\n  runner:\n    language: python\n    version: \"3.12\"\n    entrypoint: main\n  minimum_dify_version: null\ncreated_at: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\nprivacy: PRIVACY.md\nrepo: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\nverified: false\n```\n\n### 3. Provider Descriptor (`provider/agentcube.yaml`)\n\n#### Structure\n\n```yaml\nidentity:\n  author: agentcube\n  name: agentcube-code-interpreter-provider\n  label:\n    en_US: Agentcube Code Interpreter\n    zh_Hans: Agentcube 代码解释器\n  description:\n    en_US: Execute code and manage files in secure sandboxes\n    zh_Hans: 在安全沙箱中执行代码和管理文件\n  icon: icon.png\n\n# oauth_schema:\n#   identity:\n#     name: agentcube_oauth\n#     label:\n#       en_US: Agentcube OAuth\n#   config:\n#     - name: client_id\n#       label:\n#         en_US: Client ID\n#     - name: client_secret\n#       label:\n#         en_US: Client Secret\n#       type: secret-input\n\ntools:\n  - tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml\n\nextra:\n  python:\n    source: provider/agentcube.py\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- `identity` block defines provider metadata\n- `tools` list references tool descriptor files\n- `extra.python.source` points to provider implementation\n- `oauth_schema` is commented out (not active in current version)\n\n### 4. Provider Implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Any\nfrom dify_plugin import ToolProvider\nfrom dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n\nclass AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n    \"\"\"Tool provider for AgentCube Code Interpreter.\n\n    Validates credentials and manages tool registration for the\n    AgentCube integration with Dify.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Validate provider credentials.\n\n        Args:\n            credentials: Dictionary containing credential parameters\n\n        Raises:\n            ToolProviderCredentialValidationError: If credentials are invalid\n\n        Note:\n            Current implementation is a placeholder. Actual validation\n            should verify router_url and workload_manager_url connectivity.\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            # IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE\n            # Example validation:\n            # router_url = credentials.get(\"router_url\")\n            # workload_manager_url = credentials.get(\"workload_manager_url\")\n            #\n            # if not router_url or not workload_manager_url:\n            #     raise ValueError(\"Both router_url and workload_manager_url are required\")\n            #\n            # Optionally test connectivity:\n            # import requests\n            # response = requests.get(f\"{router_url}/health\", timeout=5)\n            # response.raise_for_status()\n            pass\n        except Exception as e:\n            raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n\n    # OAuth helper methods (currently not used):\n    # def _get_access_token(self) -> str:\n    #     \"\"\"Retrieve OAuth access token.\"\"\"\n    #     pass\n    #\n    # def _refresh_access_token(self) -> str:\n    #     \"\"\"Refresh OAuth access token.\"\"\"\n    #     pass\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Inherits from `dify_plugin.ToolProvider`\n- Implements `_validate_credentials()` for credential validation\n- Raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on validation failure\n- OAuth methods are commented out for future use\n- Validation should verify URL format and optionally test connectivity\n\n### 5. Tool Descriptor (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n\n#### Structure\n\n```yaml\nidentity:\n  name: agentcube-code-interpreter\n  author: agentcube\n  label:\n    en_US: Agentcube Code Interpreter\n    zh_Hans: Agentcube 代码解释器\n  description:\n    human:\n      en_US: Execute code and manage files in secure AgentCube sandboxes\n      zh_Hans: 在安全的 AgentCube 沙箱中执行代码和管理文件\n    llm:\n      en_US: A tool for executing code (Python, JavaScript, TypeScript) and managing files in secure AgentCube sandboxes. Use this when you need to run code, process files, or perform computations that require a sandboxed environment.\n      zh_Hans: 用于在安全的 AgentCube 沙箱中执行代码（Python、JavaScript、TypeScript）和管理文件的工具。当您需要运行代码、处理文件或执行需要沙箱环境的计算时使用此工具。\n\nparameters:\n  - name: router_url\n    type: string\n    required: true\n    label:\n      en_US: Router URL\n      zh_Hans: 路由器 URL\n    human_description:\n      en_US: The URL of the AgentCube Router service\n      zh_Hans: AgentCube 路由器服务的 URL\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: The base URL of the AgentCube Router service for data plane operations. This is required for all tool invocations.\n      zh_Hans: AgentCube 路由器服务的基础 URL，用于数据平面操作。所有工具调用都需要此参数。\n    form: llm\n\n  - name: workload_manager_url\n    type: string\n    required: true\n    label:\n      en_US: Workload Manager URL\n      zh_Hans: 工作负载管理器 URL\n    human_description:\n      en_US: The URL of the AgentCube Workload Manager service\n      zh_Hans: AgentCube 工作负载管理器服务的 URL\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: The base URL of the AgentCube Workload Manager service for control plane operations. This is required for creating and managing sessions.\n      zh_Hans: AgentCube 工作负载管理器服务的基础 URL，用于控制平面操作。创建和管理会话需要此参数。\n    form: llm\n\n  - name: language\n    type: select\n    required: false\n    label:\n      en_US: Language\n      zh_Hans: 编程语言\n    human_description:\n      en_US: The programming language for code execution\n      zh_Hans: 代码执行的编程语言\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: The programming language to use for code execution. Supported languages: python, javascript, typescript. Defaults to python if not specified.\n      zh_Hans: 用于代码执行的编程语言。支持的语言：python、javascript、typescript。如果未指定，默认为 python。\n    form: llm\n    options:\n      - value: python\n        label:\n          en_US: Python\n          zh_Hans: Python\n      - value: javascript\n        label:\n          en_US: JavaScript\n          zh_Hans: JavaScript\n      - value: typescript\n        label:\n          en_US: TypeScript\n          zh_Hans: TypeScript\n\n  - name: code\n    type: string\n    required: false\n    label:\n      en_US: Code\n      zh_Hans: 代码\n    human_description:\n      en_US: The code to execute\n      zh_Hans: 要执行的代码\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: The source code to execute in the specified language. Use this for code execution tasks.\n      zh_Hans: 要以指定语言执行的源代码。用于代码执行任务。\n    form: llm\n\n  - name: command\n    type: string\n    required: false\n    label:\n      en_US: Command\n      zh_Hans: 命令\n    human_description:\n      en_US: The shell command to execute\n      zh_Hans: 要执行的 Shell 命令\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: A shell command to execute in the sandbox. Use this for command-line operations. Command will be executed directly without interpretation.\n      zh_Hans: 要在沙箱中执行的 shell 命令。用于命令行操作。命令将被直接执行而不进行解释。\n    form: llm\n\n  - name: session_id\n    type: string\n    required: false\n    label:\n      en_US: Session ID\n      zh_Hans: 会话 ID\n    human_description:\n      en_US: An existing session ID to reuse\n      zh_Hans: 要重用的现有会话 ID\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: An existing session ID to reuse. If provided, the tool will connect to the existing session instead of creating a new one. Useful for maintaining state across multiple invocations.\n      zh_Hans: 要重用的现有会话 ID。如果提供，工具将连接到现有会话而不是创建新会话。用于在多次调用之间维护状态。\n    form: llm\n\n  - name: session_reuse\n    type: boolean\n    required: false\n    label:\n      en_US: Session Reuse\n      zh_Hans: 会话重用\n    human_description:\n      en_US: Whether to reuse the session\n      zh_Hans: 是否重用会话\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: If true, the session will be kept alive for reuse. If false or not provided, the session will be cleaned up after execution. Use true when you need to maintain state across multiple code executions.\n      zh_Hans: 如果为 true，会话将被保持以供重用。如果为 false 或未提供，会话将在执行后被清理。当您需要在多次代码执行之间维护状态时使用 true。\n    form: llm\n\n  - name: code_interpreter_id\n    type: string\n    required: false\n    label:\n      en_US: Code Interpreter ID\n      zh_Hans: 代码解释器 ID\n    human_description:\n      en_US: The ID of the code interpreter instance\n      zh_Hans: 代码解释器实例的 ID\n    llm_description:\n      en_US: The custom resource name/ID of the code interpreter instance. If not provided, defaults to \"my-interpreter\". This identifies which code interpreter CR to use in the cluster.\n      zh_Hans: 代码解释器实例的自定义资源名称/ID。如果未提供，默认为 \"my-interpreter\"。这标识要在集群中使用哪个代码解释器 CR。\n    form: llm\n\nextra:\n  python:\n    source: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\n```\n\n**Parameter Details:**\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Form | Purpose |\n|-----------|------|----------|------|---------|\n| `router_url` | string | true | llm | Router service URL for data plane |\n| `workload_manager_url` | string | true | llm | Workload Manager URL for control plane |\n| `language` | select | false | llm | Programming language (python/js/ts) |\n| `code` | string | false | llm | Source code to execute |\n| `command` | string | false | llm | Shell command to execute |\n| `session_id` | string | false | llm | Existing session ID for reuse |\n| `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | Whether to keep session alive |\n| `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | Custom interpreter instance name |\n\n### 6. Tool Implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n\n```python\nfrom collections.abc import Generator\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nfrom dify_plugin import Tool\nfrom dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n\nclass AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n    \"\"\"Tool for executing code and managing files in AgentCube sandboxes.\n\n    Provides integration with AgentCube's code interpreter service,\n    allowing Dify agents to execute code and perform file operations\n    in secure, isolated sandboxes.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def _invoke(\n        self,\n        tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]\n    ) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage, None, None]:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the tool with provided parameters.\n\n        Args:\n            tool_parameters: Dictionary of tool parameters\n\n        Yields:\n            ToolInvokeMessage: JSON response with execution results\n\n        Raises:\n            ToolInvokeMessage: Error message on failure\n        \"\"\"\n        try:\n            result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n            yield self.create_json_message(result)\n        except Exception as e:\n            yield self.create_text_message(f\"Error: {str(e)}\")\n\n    def execute(\n        self,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        language: str = \"python\",\n        code_interpreter_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        code: Optional[str] = None,\n        command: Optional[str] = None,\n        session_reuse: bool = False,\n        **kwargs\n    ) -> dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Execute code or command in AgentCube sandbox.\n\n        Args:\n            router_url: Router service URL\n            workload_manager_url: Workload Manager URL\n            language: Programming language (python, javascript, typescript)\n            code_interpreter_id: Custom interpreter instance name\n            session_id: Existing session ID to reuse\n            code: Source code to execute\n            command: Shell command to execute\n            session_reuse: Whether to keep session alive\n            **kwargs: Additional parameters\n\n        Returns:\n            Dictionary with execution results:\n            - success: boolean indicating success/failure\n            - output: string with stdout/output\n            - error: string with error message (if failed)\n            - session_id: session ID used\n\n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If neither code nor command provided\n            CommandExecutionError: If command execution fails\n        \"\"\"\n        # Validate inputs\n        if not code and not command:\n            raise ValueError(\"Either 'code' or 'command' parameter must be provided\")\n\n        # Set defaults\n        interpreter_name = code_interpreter_id or \"my-interpreter\"\n        namespace = \"default\"\n        ttl = 3600\n\n        # Initialize client\n        with CodeInterpreterClient(\n            name=interpreter_name,\n            namespace=namespace,\n            ttl=ttl,\n            workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url,\n            router_url=router_url,\n            session_id=session_id,\n            verbose=False,\n        ) as client:\n            try:\n                # Execute code if provided\n                if code:\n                    output = client.run_code(language=language, code=code)\n                    result = {\n                        \"success\": True,\n                        \"output\": output,\n                        \"error\": None,\n                        \"session_id\": client.session_id,\n                        \"type\": \"code\",\n                        \"language\": language,\n                    }\n                # Execute command if provided\n                elif command:\n                    output = client.execute_command(command=command)\n                    result = {\n                        \"success\": True,\n                        \"output\": output,\n                        \"error\": None,\n                        \"session_id\": client.session_id,\n                        \"type\": \"command\",\n                        \"command\": command,\n                    }\n\n                return result\n\n            except CommandExecutionError as e:\n                return {\n                    \"success\": False,\n                    \"output\": None,\n                    \"error\": str(e),\n                    \"session_id\": client.session_id,\n                    \"exit_code\": e.exit_code,\n                    \"stderr\": e.stderr,\n                }\n            except Exception as e:\n                return {\n                    \"success\": False,\n                    \"output\": None,\n                    \"error\": str(e),\n                    \"session_id\": client.session_id,\n                }\n```\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- Inherits from `dify_plugin.Tool`\n- Implements `_invoke()` as generator for Dify compatibility\n- Uses `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube-sdk`\n- Supports both code execution and command execution\n- Returns structured JSON response with execution results\n- Handles errors gracefully with detailed error information\n- Uses context manager for automatic session cleanup\n\n### 7. Plugin Dependencies (`requirements.txt`)\n\n```\ndify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\nagentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n```\n\n**Dependency Details:**\n- `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`: Dify plugin framework with compatibility bounds\n- `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`: AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter integration\n\n### 8. PCAP Analyzer Example (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n\n#### FastAPI Application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n\n##### Configuration\n\n| Environment Variable | Description | Default |\n|---------------------|-------------|---------|\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI-compatible API key | Required |\n| `OPENAI_API_BASE` | OpenAI API base URL | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n| `OPENAI_MODEL` | Model name | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager URL | From AgentCube config |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Router URL | From AgentCube config |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | Code interpreter name | `my-interpreter` |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | Sandbox namespace | `default` |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | Sandbox warmup seconds | `5` |\n\n##### Core Classes\n\n```python\nclass SandboxRunner:\n    \"\"\"Wrapper for AgentCube code interpreter client.\n\n    Provides convenience methods for file upload and command execution\n    in the PCAP analysis context.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        warmup_sec: int = 5\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Initialize sandbox runner.\n\n        Args:\n            name: Code interpreter name\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n            warmup_sec: Seconds to wait for sandbox warmup\n        \"\"\"\n        self.name = name\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.warmup_sec = warmup_sec\n        self.client: Optional[CodeInterpreterClient] = None\n\n    def upload_file(\n        self,\n        local_path: str,\n        remote_path: str\n    ) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Upload local file to sandbox.\n\n        Args:\n            local_path: Path to local file\n            remote_path: Destination path in sandbox\n\n        Returns:\n            True if upload succeeded\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.client:\n            self.client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n            return True\n        return False\n\n    def upload_bytes(\n        self,\n        data: bytes,\n        remote_path: str\n    ) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Upload bytes to sandbox file.\n\n        Args:\n            data: Bytes to write\n            remote_path: Destination path in sandbox\n\n        Returns:\n            True if upload succeeded\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.client:\n            # Write bytes to temp file then upload\n            import tempfile\n            with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(delete=False) as f:\n                f.write(data)\n                temp_path = f.name\n            try:\n                self.client.upload_file(temp_path, remote_path)\n                return True\n            finally:\n                import os\n                os.unlink(temp_path)\n        return False\n\n    def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Execute command in sandbox.\n\n        Args:\n            command: Shell command to execute\n\n        Returns:\n            Dictionary with execution results\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.client:\n            try:\n                output = self.client.execute_command(command)\n                return {\n                    \"success\": True,\n                    \"output\": output,\n                    \"error\": None,\n                }\n            except CommandExecutionError as e:\n                return {\n                    \"success\": False,\n                    \"output\": None,\n                    \"error\": str(e),\n                    \"exit_code\": e.exit_code,\n                }\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"output\": None,\n            \"error\": \"Client not initialized\",\n        }\n\n    def stop(self):\n        \"\"\"Stop the sandbox runner.\"\"\"\n        if self.client:\n            self.client.stop()\n            self.client = None\n```\n\n##### Agent Functions\n\n```python\ndef build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str):\n    \"\"\"Build a ReAct agent for code generation and execution.\n\n    Args:\n        llm: Language model instance\n        system_prompt: System prompt for the agent\n\n    Returns:\n        Configured ReAct agent\n    \"\"\"\n    from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n    from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\n\n    prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n        (\"system\", system_prompt),\n        (\"human\", \"{input}\"),\n        (\"placeholder\", \"{agent_scratchpad}\"),\n    ])\n\n    return create_react_agent(llm, tools=[], prompt=prompt)\n\ndef invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Invoke ReAct agent with user input.\n\n    Args:\n        agent: ReAct agent instance\n        user_text: User input text\n\n    Returns:\n        Agent response text\n    \"\"\"\n    from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage\n\n    result = agent.invoke({\"input\": user_text})\n    return result[\"messages\"][-1].content\n\ndef build_planner_agent(llm):\n    \"\"\"Build agent for planning analysis scripts.\n\n    Args:\n        llm: Language model instance\n\n    Returns:\n        Planner agent instance\n    \"\"\"\n    system_prompt = \"\"\"You are a PCAP analysis expert.\n    Given a PCAP file path, generate a Python script to analyze it.\n    The script should use tshark or similar tools to extract relevant information.\"\"\"\n    return build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)\n\ndef build_reporter_agent(llm):\n    \"\"\"Build agent for generating analysis reports.\n\n    Args:\n        llm: Language model instance\n\n    Returns:\n        Reporter agent instance\n    \"\"\"\n    system_prompt = \"\"\"You are a technical report writer.\n    Given PCAP analysis results, generate a comprehensive report.\"\"\"\n    return build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)\n\ndef _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Generate analysis script using planner agent.\n\n    Args:\n        agent: Planner agent instance\n        pcap_local_path: Path to PCAP file\n\n    Returns:\n        Generated Python script\n    \"\"\"\n    prompt = f\"Generate a Python script to analyze this PCAP file: {pcap_local_path}\"\n    return invoke_react_agent(agent, prompt)\n\ndef _repair_script(\n    agent,\n    prev_script: str,\n    results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Repair failed analysis script.\n\n    Args:\n        agent: Planner agent instance\n        prev_script: Previous failed script\n        results: Results from previous execution\n\n    Returns:\n        Repaired Python script\n    \"\"\"\n    error_msg = results[-1].get(\"error\", \"Unknown error\")\n    prompt = f\"\"\"The previous script failed with this error:\n    {error_msg}\n\n    Previous script:\n    {prev_script}\n\n    Please fix the script and return the corrected version.\"\"\"\n    return invoke_react_agent(agent, prompt)\n\ndef _execute_once_in_runner(\n    runner: SandboxRunner,\n    pcap_local_path: str,\n    script: str\n) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Execute analysis script once.\n\n    Args:\n        runner: SandboxRunner instance\n        pcap_local_path: Path to PCAP file\n        script: Python script to execute\n\n    Returns:\n        List of execution results\n    \"\"\"\n    results = []\n\n    # Upload PCAP file\n    remote_pcap = \"/tmp/analysis.pcap\"\n    runner.upload_file(pcap_local_path, remote_pcap)\n\n    # Write script to file\n    script_path = \"/tmp/analyze.py\"\n    runner.client.write_file(script, script_path)\n\n    # Execute script\n    result = runner.run(f\"python3 {script_path}\")\n    results.append(result)\n\n    return results\n\ndef _analyze_with_retries(\n    runner: SandboxRunner,\n    planner,\n    pcap_local_path: str,\n    max_retries: int = 2\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Analyze PCAP with retry logic.\n\n    Args:\n        runner: SandboxRunner instance\n        planner: Planner agent instance\n        pcap_local_path: Path to PCAP file\n        max_retries: Maximum number of retries\n\n    Returns:\n        Final analysis results\n    \"\"\"\n    script = _plan_script(planner, pcap_local_path)\n\n    for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\n        results = _execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_local_path, script)\n\n        if results[-1][\"success\"]:\n            return {\n                \"success\": True,\n                \"script\": script,\n                \"results\": results,\n                \"attempts\": attempt + 1,\n            }\n        elif attempt < max_retries:\n            script = _repair_script(planner, script, results)\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": False,\n        \"script\": script,\n        \"results\": results,\n        \"attempts\": max_retries + 1,\n        \"error\": \"Failed after maximum retries\",\n    }\n\ndef _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Generate analysis report.\n\n    Args:\n        agent: Reporter agent instance\n        results: Analysis execution results\n\n    Returns:\n        Generated report text\n    \"\"\"\n    results_str = \"\\n\".join([str(r) for r in results])\n    prompt = f\"Generate a report based on these analysis results:\\n{results_str}\"\n    return invoke_react_agent(agent, prompt)\n```\n\n##### FastAPI Endpoints\n\n```python\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\nimport uvicorn\n\nclass AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n    \"\"\"Response model for PCAP analysis endpoint.\"\"\"\n    script: str\n    results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n    report: str\n\napp = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n\n# Global variables\nLLM: Optional[ChatOpenAI] = None\nPLANNER: Optional[Any] = None\nREPORTER: Optional[Any] = None\n\n@app.on_event(\"startup\")\nasync def on_startup():\n    \"\"\"Initialize LLM and agents on startup.\"\"\"\n    global LLM, PLANNER, REPORTER\n\n    api_key = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n    if not api_key:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"OPENAI_API_KEY environment variable is required\")\n\n    LLM = ChatOpenAI(\n        api_key=api_key,\n        base_url=os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_BASE\", \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"),\n        model=os.getenv(\"OPENAI_MODEL\", \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"),\n    )\n\n    PLANNER = build_planner_agent(LLM)\n    REPORTER = build_reporter_agent(LLM)\n\n@app.post(\n    \"/analyze\",\n    response_model=AnalyzeResponse,\n    summary=\"Analyze PCAP file\",\n    description=\"Upload a PCAP file or provide a path for analysis\"\n)\nasync def analyze_endpoint(\n    pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None),\n    pcap_path: str = Form(None)\n) -> AnalyzeResponse:\n    \"\"\"Analyze PCAP file using AI agents and sandbox execution.\n\n    Args:\n        pcap_file: Uploaded PCAP file\n        pcap_path: Path to PCAP file on server\n\n    Returns:\n        AnalysisResponse with script, results, and report\n\n    Raises:\n        HTTPException: If analysis fails\n    \"\"\"\n    if not pcap_file and not pcap_path:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=400,\n            detail=\"Either pcap_file or pcap_path must be provided\"\n        )\n\n    try:\n        # Handle uploaded file\n        if pcap_file:\n            import tempfile\n            with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(\n                delete=False,\n                suffix=\".pcap\"\n            ) as f:\n                content = await pcap_file.read()\n                f.write(content)\n                local_pcap_path = f.name\n        else:\n            local_pcap_path = pcap_path\n\n        # Initialize sandbox runner\n        runner = SandboxRunner(\n            name=os.getenv(\"CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\", \"my-interpreter\"),\n            namespace=os.getenv(\"SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\", \"default\"),\n            warmup_sec=int(os.getenv(\"SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\", \"5\")),\n        )\n\n        # Initialize client\n        runner.client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n            name=runner.name,\n            namespace=runner.namespace,\n            router_url=os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\"),\n            workload_manager_url=os.getenv(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n        )\n\n        try:\n            # Analyze with retries\n            analysis = _analyze_with_retries(runner, PLANNER, local_pcap_path)\n\n            if not analysis[\"success\"]:\n                raise HTTPException(\n                    status_code=500,\n                    detail=f\"Analysis failed: {analysis.get('error')}\"\n                )\n\n            # Generate report\n            report = _report(REPORTER, analysis[\"results\"])\n\n            return AnalyzeResponse(\n                script=analysis[\"script\"],\n                results=analysis[\"results\"],\n                report=report,\n            )\n\n        finally:\n            # Cleanup\n            runner.stop()\n            if pcap_file:\n                import os\n                os.unlink(local_pcap_path)\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=str(e))\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    uvicorn.run(\n        app,\n        host=os.getenv(\"SERVER_HOST\", \"0.0.0.0\"),\n        port=int(os.getenv(\"SERVER_PORT\", \"8000\")),\n        reload=os.getenv(\"SERVER_RELOAD\", \"true\").lower() == \"true\",\n    )\n```\n\n#### Dependencies (`requirements.txt`)\n\n```\nfastapi==0.120.0\nuvicorn==0.38.0\nlangchain==1.0.2\nlangchain-classic==1.0.0\nlangchain-community==0.4.1\nlangchain-core==1.0.1\nlangchain-openai==1.0.1\nlangchain-text-splitters==1.0.0\nlanggraph==1.0.1\nlanggraph-checkpoint==3.0.0\nlanggraph-prebuilt==1.0.1\nlanggraph-sdk==0.2.9\nlangsmith==0.4.38\nparamiko==4.0.0\npython-multipart==0.0.20\nagentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n```\n\n#### Dockerfile\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Install dependencies\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN uv venv && uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Copy agentcube SDK (vendored from monorepo)\nCOPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\n\n# Copy application\nCOPY pcap_analyzer.py .\n\n# Set Python path\nENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\n\n# Expose port\nEXPOSE 8000\n\n# Run application\nCMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n```\n\n#### Kubernetes Deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: pcap-analyzer\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: pcap-analyzer\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: pcap-analyzer\n        image: pcap-analyzer:latest\n        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8000\n          protocol: TCP\n        env:\n        - name: OPENAI_API_KEY\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n              key: openai-api-key\n        - name: OPENAI_API_BASE\n          value: \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"\n        - name: OPENAI_MODEL\n          value: \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"\n        - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n          value: \"http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\"\n        - name: ROUTER_URL\n          value: \"http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\"\n        - name: CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\n          value: \"my-interpreter\"\n        - name: SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\n          value: \"default\"\n        - name: SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\n          value: \"5\"\n        - name: SERVER_HOST\n          value: \"0.0.0.0\"\n        - name: SERVER_PORT\n          value: \"8000\"\n        - name: SERVER_RELOAD\n          value: \"false\"\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            cpu: 200m\n            memory: 100Mi\n          limits:\n            cpu: \"1\"\n            memory: 1Gi\n        command: [\"uv\"]\n        args: [\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Secret\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n  namespace: default\ntype: Opaque\nstringData:\n  openai-api-key: \"your-api-key-here\"\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: pcap-analyzer\n  ports:\n  - port: 8000\n    targetPort: 8000\n    protocol: TCP\n  type: ClusterIP\n```\n\n## Configuration Management\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Required | Default |\n|----------|---------|----------|---------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Router service URL | Yes (for tool) | - |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager URL | Yes (for tool) | - |\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI API key (PCAP example) | Yes | - |\n| `OPENAI_API_BASE` | OpenAI API base URL | No | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n| `OPENAI_MODEL` | Model name | No | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | Code interpreter name | No | `my-interpreter` |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | Sandbox namespace | No | `default` |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | Warmup seconds | No | `5` |\n\n### Configuration Resolution Order\n\nFor each setting, resolution follows this priority:\n1. Tool parameter (highest)\n2. Environment variable\n3. Code default (lowest)\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass DifyPluginError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for Dify plugin errors.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CredentialValidationError(DifyPluginError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when credential validation fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass ToolExecutionError(DifyPluginError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when tool execution fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass SessionManagementError(DifyPluginError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session management fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Error Type | Handling |\n|----------|------------|----------|\n| Missing router_url | ValueError | Return error message to Dify |\n| Missing workload_manager_url | ValueError | Return error message to Dify |\n| Invalid credentials | ToolProviderCredentialValidationError | Provider-level rejection |\n| Command execution failure | CommandExecutionError | Return structured error |\n| Session creation failure | SessionError | Retry or fail gracefully |\n| Network timeout | requests.Timeout | Return timeout error |\n| Malformed response | ValueError | Return parsing error |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Component | Test Cases |\n|-----------|------------|\n| `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider._validate_credentials()` | - Valid credentials pass<br>- Missing router_url raises error<br>- Missing workload_manager_url raises error<br>- Invalid URL format raises error<br>- Network errors are handled |\n| `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool.execute()` | - Code execution with Python<br>- Code execution with JavaScript<br>- Command execution<br>- Session reuse behavior<br>- Error handling returns structured response<br>- Both code and command raises error<br>- Neither code nor command raises error |\n| `SandboxRunner` | - File upload succeeds<br>- Bytes upload succeeds<br>- Command execution returns results<br>- Command failure captures error<br>- Stop cleans up properly |\n| `_plan_script()` | - Generates valid Python script<br>- Handles different PCAP scenarios<br>- Returns string output |\n| `_repair_script()` | - Fixes syntax errors<br>- Handles execution errors<br>- Improves script iteratively |\n| `_execute_once_in_runner()` | - Uploads file correctly<br>- Writes script correctly<br>- Executes and captures output<br>- Captures errors |\n| `_analyze_with_retries()` | - Success on first attempt<br>- Retries on failure<br>- Fails after max retries<br>- Tracks attempt count |\n| `_report()` | - Generates report text<br>- Handles empty results<br>- Formats output correctly |\n| FastAPI endpoints | - Startup with valid config<br>- Startup fails without API key<br>- Analyze with uploaded file<br>- Analyze with file path<br>- Missing both parameters raises 400<br>- Analysis failure raises 500 |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Test Cases |\n|----------|------------|\n| Plugin loading | - Manifest loads successfully<br>- Provider registers<br>- Tool registers<br>- All parameters accessible |\n| Tool invocation | - Simple code execution<br>- Complex code execution<br>- Long-running code<br>- File operations<br>- Session management |\n| Session lifecycle | - Create session<br>- Reuse session<br>- Session cleanup<br>- Concurrent sessions |\n| Error recovery | - Network failures<br>- Timeout handling<br>- Invalid parameters<br>- Malformed responses |\n| PCAP analyzer E2E | - Upload and analyze<br>- Path-based analysis<br>- Error scenarios<br>- Multiple analyses |\n\n### Mock Tests\n\n- Mock `CodeInterpreterClient` for tool tests\n- Mock `ChatOpenAI` for agent tests\n- Mock file system for upload tests\n- Mock HTTP requests for network tests\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Credential Management:**\n   - Credentials passed via tool parameters (not stored)\n   - No credential logging in verbose mode\n   - URLs validated before use\n\n2. **Code Execution:**\n   - All code runs in isolated sandboxes\n   - Resource limits enforced by Kubernetes\n   - Timeouts prevent runaway processes\n\n3. **File Operations:**\n   - File paths validated and sanitized\n   - Uploads restricted to allowed types\n   - Download paths prevent directory traversal\n\n4. **Network Security:**\n   - HTTPS required for production\n   - TLS certificate validation\n   - Connection pooling prevents resource exhaustion\n\n5. **Session Management:**\n   - Session IDs not exposed in logs\n   - Sessions expire via TTL\n   - Cleanup on tool completion\n\n6. **Input Validation:**\n   - All parameters validated before use\n   - Command injection prevention\n   - Code execution in controlled environments\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n1. **Connection Pooling:**\n   - Shared HTTP session across requests\n   - Configurable pool sizes\n   - Connection reuse reduces latency\n\n2. **Session Management:**\n   - Session reuse for related operations\n   - Lazy session creation\n   - Automatic cleanup\n\n3. **Timeout Configuration:**\n   - Configurable per-call timeouts\n   - Default 120-second timeout\n   - Separate connect and read timeouts\n\n4. **Memory Management:**\n   - Streaming for large file downloads\n   - Context managers for cleanup\n   - Limited file upload sizes\n\n5. **Concurrency:**\n   - Support for concurrent tool invocations\n   - Thread-safe HTTP sessions\n   - Independent session management\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Plugin Runtime Dependencies\n\n```\ndify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\nagentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n```\n\n### PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n\n```\nfastapi==0.120.0\nuvicorn==0.38.0\nlangchain==1.0.2\nlangchain-classic==1.0.0\nlangchain-community==0.4.1\nlangchain-core==1.0.1\nlangchain-openai==1.0.1\nlangchain-text-splitters==1.0.0\nlanggraph==1.0.1\nlanggraph-checkpoint==3.0.0\nlanggraph-prebuilt==1.0.1\nlanggraph-sdk==0.2.9\nlangsmith==0.4.38\nparamiko==4.0.0\npython-multipart==0.0.20\nagentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n```\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Additional Languages:**\n   - Support for more languages (Go, Rust, Java)\n   - Language-specific optimizations\n\n2. **Advanced File Operations:**\n   - File system browsing\n   - Batch operations\n   - File streaming\n\n3. **Session Features:**\n   - Session persistence across restarts\n   - Session templates\n   - Session metrics\n\n4. **Tool Enhancements:**\n   - Output visualization\n   - Progress reporting\n   - Result caching\n\n5. **Integration Improvements:**\n   - OAuth authentication\n   - Custom tool configurations\n   - Plugin marketplace support\n\n6. **Monitoring and Observability:**\n   - Request/response logging\n   - Performance metrics\n   - Error tracking\n\n7. **Developer Experience:**\n   - Local development mode\n   - Testing utilities\n   - Debugging tools\n\n8. **Security Enhancements:**\n   - Fine-grained permissions\n   - Audit logging\n   - Resource quotas","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-036/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-036/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-036/design.md","time":{"start":1775888783964,"end":1775888783974}}}}
